    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but i read online that medical grade honey (manuka) is actually used in hospitals for wound care because it's so good at killing bacteria and helping cells regenerate. if i can just get some of that kind, wouldn't that be better than just using antibiotic cream? im just worried about how much the clinic will charge me if i go in for something that might just be a superficial cut.",
